  "notes": [
    {
      "id": "2ec26f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralTitle",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 0,
      "content": "IMPORTANT MAJOR DETAILS",
      "contentHtml": null
    },
    {
      "id": "33c26f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 1,
      "content": "The Linguistics and Asian Languages and Cultures major combines the basic courses of the general linguistics program with that of East Asian languages and cultures. Students are able to study the civilizations of China, Korea, Japan and India, and enrich their knowledge about the nature, grammar, and history of human language at the same time. Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for this major. To be considered for this major, you must complete the following courses by the end of spring before transfer: One year of college level coursework in the declared language OR At least one year of high school in which the primary language of instruction was the declared language. Completion of introduction to linguistics and introduction to linguistic anthropology are STRONGLY RECOMMENDED . Completion of two years of college foreign language is STRONGLY RECOMMENDED . A placement exam for a language offered at UCLA may be taken upon transfer to test out of or make progress toward the major language requirement. All courses must be taken for a letter grade. For more information regarding this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit https:// linguistics.ucla.edu and https:// admission.ucla.edu . PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses.",
      "contentHtml": "<p>The Linguistics and Asian Languages and Cultures major combines the basic courses of the general linguistics program with that of East Asian languages and cultures. Students are able to study the civilizations of China, Korea, Japan and India, and enrich their knowledge about the nature, grammar, and history of human language at the same time.</p><p><br></p><p>Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for this major.</p><p><br></p><p>To be considered for this major, you must complete the following courses by the end of spring before transfer:</p><ul><li>One year of college level coursework in the declared language OR</li><li>At least one year of high school in which the primary language of instruction was the declared language.</li></ul><p>Completion of introduction to linguistics and introduction to linguistic anthropology are <strong>STRONGLY RECOMMENDED</strong>.</p><p>Completion of two years of college foreign language is <strong>STRONGLY RECOMMENDED</strong>. A placement exam for a language offered at UCLA may be taken upon transfer to test out of or make progress toward the major language requirement.</p><p>All courses must be taken for a letter grade.</p><p><br></p><p>For more information regarding this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit <u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">https://</u><a href=\"http://www.linguistics.ucla.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">linguistics.ucla.edu</a> and <u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">https://</u><a href=\"http://www.admission.ucla.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">admission.ucla.edu</a>.</p><p><br></p><p>PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses.</p>"
    }
